<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-19T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-19T11:00:00-05:00" n="1030" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1030">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">819.011/9–1945: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Donnelly</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Panamá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-19T11:00:00-05:00">September
                                    19, 1945—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>851. The committee studying proposed constitution will vote today on
                            articles relating to nationalization of commerce. While proposed
                            compromise represents a substantial improvement over original draft, the
                            President has again informed me that he still feels that nationalization
                            of commerce should take the form of separate legislation and <pb facs="1288" n="1274" xml:id="pg_1274"/> that he will use his
                            influence in this direction at the appropriate time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Donnelly</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>